23/12/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- Chief of Staff Hilmi Ozkok met with visiting Israeli counterpart General Dan Halutz on Thursday (22 December) to discuss areas in which military co-operation could be further strengthened. 
They also talked about Iran and its suspected nuclear activities, the global threat of terrorism and the Mideast peace process.
Separately Thursday, former US Ambassador to Turkey Mark Parris praised Ankaraâs role in the process and said stabilisation of the Middle East would be impossible without Turkey. 
He said Washington can rely on Ankara for help in strengthening democracy in the region.
